http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Young-Chef-Olympiad/article14009928.ece

The International Institute of Hotel Management is all set to host the second edition of the Young Chef Olympiad 2016, a mega contest for culinary students across the globe. The six-day event is being held in New Delhi, Mumbai, Bengaluru and Kolkata. It will begin on January 27 at Talkatora Indoor Stadium in New Delhi. It will be followed by a cook-off in the four cities culminating in a grand finale in Kolkata on February 1.The first round of the Olympiad is to be held on January 29 in Bengaluru. Young chefs from 11 countries, including Australia, Malaysia, Nepal, Philippines, Mexico, Mauritius, are expected to participate.